theorem closure_union_interior_compl_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    closure (A : Set X) ∪ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro _
    trivial
  · intro _
    by_cases hx : x ∈ closure (A : Set X)
    · exact Or.inl hx
    · -- Show `x ∈ interior (Aᶜ)`
      -- `x` lies in the open set `(closure A)ᶜ`, which is contained in `Aᶜ`.
      have hxCompl : x ∈ ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) := hx
      have hOpen : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
        isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
      have hSub : (closure (A : Set X) : Set X)ᶜ ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
        intro y hy
        by_contra hyA
        exact hy (subset_closure hyA)
      have : x ∈ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
        mem_interior.2 ⟨(closure (A : Set X))ᶜ, hSub, hOpen, hxCompl⟩
      exact Or.inr this
